@NODE "datasheet" "bitmap_ic/datasheet (information)"


    NAME
        @{"bitmap_ic" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/bitmap_ic/MAIN"} -- Create image object using datatypes

    SUPERCLASS
        imageclass

    REQUIRES
        None.

    DESCRIPTION
        This image class can create an image given the name of a source
        file. It uses the datatypes system to create a bitmap used for
        rendering the image. Bitmap supports drawing itself in a selected
        state, and supports transparent images provided that the datatype
        supports transparency.

        Instead of a source file name, a ready-to-use bitmap can be passed
        with @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}.

    METHODS
        @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63} -- Create the bitmap image.  Passed to superclass, then @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}.

        @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66} -- Get object attributes.  Passed to superclass first.

        @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} -- Set object attributes.  Passed to superclass first.

        @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70} -- Set object notification attributes.  Passed to
            superclassfirst.

        @{"IM_DRAW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/imageclass.h/File" 183} -- Renders the image.  Overrides the superclass.

        All other methods are passed to the superclass, including @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64}.

    ATTRIBUTES
        IA_TopEdge (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
        IA_LeftEdge (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
        @{"IA_Width" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/imageclass.h/File" 36} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
        @{"IA_Height" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/imageclass.h/File" 37} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Set position and size of the image. If given, these must be
            greater then or equal to the maximum dimensions of the bitmaps
            used.

            If the image size is larger than one of the bitmap sizes, the
            bitmap will be drawn centered within in the image. The area
            surrounding the bitmap is @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500} erased!

            Defaults to the maximum of the dimensions of the normal and
            selected bitmaps.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_SourceFile" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 32} (@{"STRPTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 67})
            Source file name of the image file to create the bitmap from,
            using the datatypes system.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_Screen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 35} (@{"struct Screen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 133} *)
            Pointer to the screen to use the image on. This attribute MUST
            be provided when creating an object of this class using the
            datatypes system.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_Precision" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 38} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})
            Precision to use when obtaining colors. See the PRECISION_
            defines in <@{"graphics/view.h" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/view.h/File"}>

            Defaults to @{"PRECISION_ICON" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/view.h/File" 240}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_Masking" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 41} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
            If set to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, the image will be drawn using a transparent
            mask if the image source contains a transparent color.

            Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 44} (@{"struct BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/gfx.h/File" 46} *)
            Instead of letting the class create the bitmap using datatypes,
            you can create your own bitmap and pass it to the class.
            If you supply your own bitmap, you MUST set @{"BITMAP_Width" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 47}
            and @{"BITMAP_Height" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 50} too.
            Either @{"BITMAP_SourceFile" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 32} or @{"BITMAP_BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 44} must be given.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_Width" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 47} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
        @{"BITMAP_Height" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 50} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Set the dimensions of your own bitmap passed with
            @{"BITMAP_BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 44}, or get the dimensions of the bitmap created
            by the datatype.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_MaskPlane" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 53} (@{"APTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 49})
            A mask plane. Only set this if you supply your own bitmap
            with @{"BITMAP_BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 44}.
            The mask plane will only be used if @{"BITMAP_Masking" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 41} is @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

            Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_SelectSourceFile" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 56} (@{"STRPTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 67})
            Source file name of the selected state image to create the
            bitmap from, using the datatypes system.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_SelectBitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 59} (@{"struct BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/gfx.h/File" 46} *)
            Your own bitmap to use for the selected state.
            If you supply your own bitmap, you MUST set @{"BITMAP_SelectWidth" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 62}
            and @{"BITMAP_SelectHeight" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 65} too.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_SelectWidth" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 62} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
        @{"BITMAP_SelectHeight" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 65} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Set the dimensions of your own selected statebitmap passed
            with @{"BITMAP_SelectBitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 59}, or get the dimensions of the selected
            state bitmap created by the datatype.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_SelectMaskPlane" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 68} (@{"APTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 49})
            A mask plane for the selected state bitmap. Only set this if
            you supply your own bitmap with @{"BITMAP_SelectBitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 59}.
            The mask plane will only be used if @{"BITMAP_Masking" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 41} is @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

            Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_OffsetX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 71} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
        @{"BITMAP_OffsetY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 74} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Together with @{"BITMAP_BitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 44}, @{"BITMAP_Width" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 47} and @{"BITMAP_Height" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 50}
            these attributes determine which part of the bitmap to use
            for the image.
            These attributes will be ignored if the bitmap was created
            by the class using datatypes.

            Defaults to 0.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"BITMAP_SelectOffsetX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 77} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
        @{"BITMAP_SelectOffsetY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 80} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Together with @{"BITMAP_SelectBitMap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 59}, @{"BITMAP_SelectWidth" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 62} and
            @{"BITMAP_SelectHeight" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/images/bitmap.h/File" 65} these attributes determine which part
            of the bitmap to use for the selected state image.
            These attributes will be ignored if the bitmap was created
            by the class using datatypes.

            Defaults to 0.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

@ENDNODE
@NODE "BITMAP_GetClass" "bitmap_ic/BITMAP_GetClass()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"BITMAP_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/bitmap.h/File" 23} -- Gets the pointer to the bitmap class.@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        bitmap_class = @{"BITMAP_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/bitmap.h/File" 23}();
        D0

        Class * @{"BITMAP_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/bitmap.h/File" 23}(@{"VOID" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 24});@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Obtains the pointer to the BitMap image class for use with
        @{"NewObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/NewObject"}.  This function always returns a valid pointer so
        you do not need to check it.  The reason is that if the library
        opens fine, then the pointer returned is already setup.  (Of course
        this implies that if opening the library fails, you shouldn't be
        calling this.)

        Note that this function does not create the class, that is done
        when the class library is opened.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Nothing.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        bitmap_class - Pointer to the BitMap image class.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}

@ENDNODE
